i-search-my-outbound-activity-in-mandrill\">inside the application</a>. Mandrill searches utilize <a href=\"http://lucene.apache.org/core/old_versioned_docs/versions/3_5_0/queryparsersyntax.html\">Lucene queries</a>, which means you can search by a single term, phrases (surrounded with double quotes), multiple terms (using the Boolean operators AND, OR, and NOT) and wildcards (* for multiple character wildcards and ? for single character). And by default, Mandrill searches all indexed fields, including any <a href=\"http://help.mandrill.com/entries/21786413-using-custom-message-metadata\">custom metadata</a> that you\'ve added. All that information is just one search field away.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"html\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:2:\"en\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:4:\"term\";s:6:\"how-to\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:2:\"en\";}}}}}i:66;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:2:\"en\";s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Email as a Service as a Service\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:2:\"en\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:2:{s:4:\"href\";s:61:\"http://blog.mandrill.com/email-as-a-service-as-a-service.html\";s:3:\"rel\";s:9:\"alternate\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:2:\"en\";}}s:7:\"updated\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"2012-10-15T00:00:00Z\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:2:\"en\";}}s:6:\"author\";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:2:\"en\";s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:2:{s:4:\"name\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Loren\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:2:\"en\";}}s:3:\"uri\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"http://blog.mandrill.com/author/Loren.html\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:2:\"en\";}}}}}}s:2:\"id\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"tag:blog.mandrill.com,2012-10-15:/email-as-a-service-as-a-service.html/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:2:\"en\";}}s:7:\"summary\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1049:\"<p>By now, you know that Mandrill provides tools for building out your email infrastructure. What you may not know, however, is that the tools can also be used to pass value down the chain to your own customers. Today we\'re going to examine how one of our customers has done just that with some of our more advanced email platform features.</p>\n\n<p>In their own words:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>\"<em>Mandrill\'s turnkey email platform allowed us to migrate from our internal postfix system to their ESP in a couple of days. That included development of our <strong>amazing new \"Email History\" feature which allows our customers to instantly see deliverability, opens, and clicks for every email</strong> handled by our system.</em></p>\n\n<p>\"<em>Our new email infrastructure has improved deliverability, vastly increased customer confidence in our system, and reduced support load for both us and our customers.</em>\"  -Alan Pinstein, cofounder, <a href=\"http://tourbuzz.net\">Tourbuzz.net</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Read on to learn how they did it.</p>\n\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"html\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:2:\"en\";}}s:8